scope_of_work.problem: Following an investigation into a fault on ACU 4 it was found that system 1 has a refrigerant leak and needs repairs
scope_of_work.scope:
1. Isolate System 1 and carry out safety checks
2. Refrigerant recovery not required due to loss of refrigerant
3. Pressure test system using OFN
4. Locate and seal any minor leaks
5. Pressure test system to ensure no further leaks are present
6. Evacuate system to its suitable Torr reading and complete a vacuum rise test
7. Charge the system with fresh R410A Refrigerant 
8. Remove isolations and test operation
9. Update F-Gas Records if made available by site
10. Service report to be issued upon completion of works
scope_of_work.justification: ACU 4 provides cooling for the EPH UPS room and is currently running on one refrigerant circuit. As the room temperature will increase to higher than optimum temperature therefore leading to the possibility of the UPS system overheating and failing.
scope_of_work.non_approval_effect: ACU 4 provides cooling for the EPH UPS room and is currently running on one refrigerant circuit. As the room temperature will increase to higher than optimum temperature therefore leading to the possibility of the UPS system overheating and failing.

scope_of_work.problem: The existing single steel door leading out to DRUPS 1 and 2 from the DC grey space corridor is in a very poor state of repair. The doors are 20+ years old and form part of both the emergency exit route and security perimeter. The door needs replacement.
scope_of_work.scope: Set up alternative escape route and barrier off the work area, - temporary removal of access control equipment, - removal of the existing door and disposal off-site, - replacement/installation of a new door and reinstatement of the the access control - commissioning of the security controls. Allowances have been made for making good the area around the door opening and also for the attendance of a security guard who will remain in post during the door replacement.

scope_of_work.non_approval_effect: The doors will continue to corrode and become difficult to open, causing health and safety issues.
